---
import Base from '~/layouts/Base.astro';

const description =
  'Privacy notice under Art. 13 GDPR for the private academic website of Rouven Jahnke.';

// Update this when the substance of the privacy notice changes.
const STAND = 'April 2026';
---

<Base title="Privacy" description={description} minimal>
  <article class="prose">
    <header class="page-header">
      <p class="page-header__eyebrow">Legal</p>
      <h1>Privacy notice</h1>
      <p class="page-header__lede">
        Information about the processing of personal data when this
        website is accessed, under Art. 13 of the EU General Data
        Protection Regulation (GDPR).
      </p>
    </header>

    <h2>1. Controller</h2>
    <p>
      The controller within the meaning of Art. 4 No. 7 GDPR is the
      natural person named in the <a href="/impressum">legal notice</a>.
    </p>

    <p>
      This notice covers <strong>rouvenjahnke.com</strong>. A separate
      application is reachable at the subdomain
      <strong>cloud.rouvenjahnke.com</strong> and is described in
      section&nbsp;4.2 below; its internal processing lies outside the
      scope of this notice.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Data collected on access</h2>
    <p>
      When this website is accessed, the hosting provider processes
      technical access data in server-side log files:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>IP address of the requesting device</li>
      <li>date and time of the request</li>
      <li>requested URL and HTTP status code</li>
      <li>amount of data transferred</li>
      <li>user agent (browser, operating system, language)</li>
      <li>referrer URL, if transmitted by the browser</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      This website uses no analytics, tracking or profiling services.
      <strong>No cookies are set.</strong> There are no forms, and no
      server-side data storage beyond the log files described above.
      Contact is made exclusively via the email address given in the
      legal notice; in that case the content of the message is stored
      for the purpose of handling the enquiry.
    </p>
    <p>
      For the dismissal of the informational notice shown at the
      bottom of each page, the browser stores a single
      <code>localStorage</code> entry
      (<code>site-notice-dismissed</code>). The value is a plain flag,
      contains no personal data, is never transmitted to any server,
      and can be removed at any time in the browser&rsquo;s storage
      settings. The processing is covered by § 25(2) no. 2 TDDDG
      (strictly necessary for a function explicitly requested by the
      user when dismissing the notice).
    </p>

    <h2>3. Purpose and legal basis</h2>
    <p>
      The log data is processed for the reliable operation, stability
      and security of the website, in particular to defend against
      abusive access. The legal basis is Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR; the
      legitimate interest follows from the purposes stated above. For
      email correspondence the legal basis is Art. 6(1)(b) or (f) GDPR.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Recipients and processors</h2>

    <h3>4.1 Main website (rouvenjahnke.com)</h3>
    <p>
      The main website is hosted by Cloudflare, Inc.
      (<a href="https://www.cloudflare.com" rel="noopener noreferrer">www.cloudflare.com</a>)
      on the Cloudflare Pages platform. Cloudflare processes the data
      described under section 2 as a processor within the meaning of
      Art. 28 GDPR on the basis of a corresponding data processing
      agreement.
    </p>

    <h3>4.2 Subdomain cloud.rouvenjahnke.com</h3>

    <h4>4.2.1 Hosting</h4>
    <p>
      The subdomain <code>cloud.rouvenjahnke.com</code> runs on shared
      infrastructure provided by Hetzner Online GmbH, Industriestraße
      25, 91710 Gunzenhausen, Germany
      (<a href="https://www.hetzner.com" rel="noopener noreferrer">www.hetzner.com</a>).
      Hetzner processes access and server data for that subdomain as
      a processor within the meaning of Art. 28 GDPR on the basis of
      a corresponding data processing agreement.
    </p>

    <h4>4.2.2 Nextcloud application</h4>
    <p>
      The subdomain hosts a private Nextcloud instance. The Nextcloud
      service is a separate application with its own processing
      context. Accessing it may set strictly necessary session cookies
      for authentication and CSRF protection; these cookies are set
      by the Nextcloud software itself and are described in the
      privacy information provided inside that application. No
      personal data is exchanged between <code>rouvenjahnke.com</code>
      and <code>cloud.rouvenjahnke.com</code>.
    </p>

    <h4>4.2.3 Event registration forms</h4>
    <p>
      The subdomain may host forms that allow you to register for, or
      book a place at, a specific event (for example events with
      catering or drinks). If you submit such a form, the following
      personal data is processed: your name and email address,
      whether you attend with a companion and, if so, the name of
      that companion, as well as any free-text remarks you choose to
      provide (such as allergies, dietary requirements or other
      information relevant to organising the event).
    </p>
    <p>
      Form submissions are handled on the Hetzner infrastructure
      described in section 4.2.1 by a self-hosted workflow-automation
      tool (n8n). As part of the workflow, the form contents are
      forwarded as an email message so that the registration can be
      processed manually. The email is dispatched via the Gmail
      service operated by Google LLC, 1600 Amphitheatre Parkway,
      Mountain View, CA 94043, USA (EU representative: Google
      Ireland Limited, Gordon House, Barrow Street, Dublin 4,
      Ireland). In the course of delivering and storing the message,
      Google processes the sender and recipient addresses and the
      content of the email in accordance with its own privacy policy
      (<a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" rel="noopener noreferrer">policies.google.com/privacy</a>).
      This applies only to email traffic originating from
      registration forms on the subdomain;
      <code>rouvenjahnke.com</code> does not send any automated email.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Legal basis.</strong> Processing of registration data
      is based on Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR (performance of the registration
      arrangement and pre-contractual steps at your request). Where
      you voluntarily disclose health-related information such as
      allergies or dietary requirements, that information constitutes
      a special category of personal data within the meaning of
      Art. 9(1) GDPR; its processing is based on your explicit
      consent under Art. 9(2)(a) GDPR, which you can withdraw at any
      time with effect for the future. Providing any of the requested
      data is voluntary; if it is not provided, the registration
      cannot be processed.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Companions.</strong> If you enter a companion&rsquo;s
      name, you are responsible for informing that person about the
      processing described in this notice; the companion may
      exercise the rights listed in section 7 directly against the
      controller.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Retention.</strong> Registration data is kept only as
      long as is needed to organise and follow up on the respective
      event (for example to compile attendee, catering or drinks
      lists) and is deleted without undue delay after the event,
      unless a statutory retention obligation or the establishment or
      defence of legal claims requires longer storage.
    </p>

    <p>No transfer of data to any further third parties takes place.</p>

    <h2>5. Transfers to third countries</h2>
    <p>
      To the extent that the hosting provider processes personal data
      in a third country outside the EU or EEA, this is carried out on
      the basis of an adequacy decision (Art. 45 GDPR) or appropriate
      safeguards, in particular the Standard Contractual Clauses of the
      European Commission (Art. 46(2)(c) GDPR).
    </p>
    <p>
      In addition, where emails are dispatched via Gmail as part of
      the event-registration flow described in section 4.2.3, the
      sender and recipient addresses and the content of the
      respective emails are transferred to Google LLC in the United
      States. The transfer is based on the EU-US Data Privacy
      Framework (Commission Implementing Decision (EU) 2023/1795,
      Art. 45 GDPR), under which Google LLC is certified, and
      additionally on the Standard Contractual Clauses of the
      European Commission (Art. 46(2)(c) GDPR).
    </p>

    <h2>6. Retention</h2>
    <p>
      Log data is retained for the usual period set by the hosting
      provider (typically a few days up to a few weeks) and is then
      deleted or anonymised to the extent that no personal reference
      remains. Email content is retained until the enquiry has been
      dealt with and, beyond that, only to the extent required by
      statutory retention obligations.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      You have the following rights vis-à-vis the controller at any
      time:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>access to the data processed about you (Art. 15 GDPR)</li>
      <li>rectification of inaccurate data (Art. 16 GDPR)</li>
      <li>erasure (Art. 17 GDPR)</li>
      <li>restriction of processing (Art. 18 GDPR)</li>
      <li>data portability (Art. 20 GDPR)</li>
      <li>objection to processing (Art. 21 GDPR)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      An informal message to the email address given in the
      <a href="/impressum">legal notice</a> is sufficient to exercise
      these rights.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority</h2>
    <p>
      You have the right to lodge a complaint with a data-protection
      supervisory authority about the processing of your personal data
      (Art. 77 GDPR). The locally competent authority for the
      controller is:
    </p>
    <address>
      Der Hamburgische Beauftragte für<br />
      Datenschutz und Informationsfreiheit (HmbBfDI)<br />
      Ludwig-Erhard-Straße 22, 7. OG<br />
      20459 Hamburg, Germany<br />
      Phone: +49 40 428 54-4040<br />
      Email: <a href="mailto:mailbox@datenschutz.hamburg.de">mailbox@datenschutz.hamburg.de</a><br />
      Web: <a href="https://datenschutz-hamburg.de" rel="noopener noreferrer">datenschutz-hamburg.de</a>
    </address>

    <hr />

    <p>
      <small>Last updated: {STAND}.</small>
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>
